y over this period, she determines that television themes and interpretations largely remained the same. The greater change was in the production and presentation, particularly in the role of professional historians, as journalists emerged not only as the new producers of Canadian history on CBC television, but also as the new content authorities. A critique of public history through the lens of political economy, Recasting History reveals the conflicts, compromises, and controversies that have shaped the CBC version of the Canadian past.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aDocumentary television programszCanadaxHistory and criticism. 0aHistorical television programszCanadaxHistory and criticism. 0aHistory on television. 0aTelevision and historyzCanada. 0aTelevision broadcasting policyzCanadaxHistory. 0aTelevisionxSocial aspectszCanada. 7aHISTORY / Canada / General.2bisacsh1 aMonica, MacDonald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077355808340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773558083423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773558083/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles